{{Infobox book | name = Hidden Terrors: The Truth About U.S. Police Operations in Latin America | image = File:Hidden Terrors.jpg | author = [[A. J. Langguth]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[American foreign policy]] | publisher = [[Pantheon Books]] | pub_date = 1978 | pages = | isbn = 0394406745 | dewey = | congress = | oclc = }} '''''Hidden Terrors: The Truth About U.S. Police Operations in Latin America''''' is a 1978 book about [[American foreign policy in Brazil]] and [[Uruguay–United States relations|Uruguay]] in the 1960s and early 1970s by the journalist [[A. J. Langguth]].
