{{Infobox settlement |official_name =Picão |other_name = |settlement_type =Settlement |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_map = |mapsize = 350px |map_caption = |pushpin_map =Principe |pushpin_label_position =bottom |pushpin_mapsize= |pushpin_map_caption =Location on [[Príncipe Island]] |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name =[[São Tomé and Príncipe]] |subdivision_type1 =Autonomous Region |subdivision_name1 =[[Autonomous Region of Príncipe|Príncipe]] |unit_pref = |area_footnotes = |area_total_km2 = |area_land_km2 = |population_as_of =2012 |population_footnotes = |population_note = |population_total =278 |population_density_km2 = |timezone1 = UTC |utc_offset1 = +0 |coordinates = {{coord|1.6657|N|7.431|E|display=inline,title}} |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |website = }} '''Picão''' is a settlement in the northeastern part of [[Príncipe Island]] in [[São Tomé and Príncipe]]. Its population is 278 (2012 census).<ref name=census12>[https://www.ine.st/phocadownload/userupload/Documentos/DADOS%20LOCALIDADE%20PROJE%C3%87%C3%95ES/Publica%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20dos%20Resultados%20sobre%20Localidades%20-%20IV%20RGPH%202012.pdf 2012 detailed census São Tomé e Príncipe], [[Instituto Nacional de Estatística (São Tomé and Príncipe)|Instituto Nacional de Estatística]]</ref> The settlement is located northeast of the island capital [[Santo António]]. To the northeast is [[Belo Monte, São Tomé and Príncipe|Belo Monte]], to the east is Praia Grande, a beach, to the south is [[Praia Inhame, Príncipe|Praia Inhame]] and to the west is the settlement of [[Aeroporto, Príncipe|Aeroporto]].
